metadata.name: Why is a Raven Like a Writing Desk?
metadata.description:
¨ Why is a Raven Like a Writing Desk? ¨
(Ink Drawing on paper and Digital Art)
(7992x7992, 32bit)

Dedicated to Lewis Carroll and inspired by his work, Alice in Wonderland.

It illustrates the sane portion of the craziness of the Mad Hatters question, without literally illustrating his words… but looking as they should if one tried to look at them as one should.

- Why is a Raven Like a Writing Desk?

- “Because it can produce very few notes, whom they are very flat; and it is NEVER put with the wrong end in front”.

                                                                                                                                            …Lewis Carrol
